dients like <u><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/17524126/" target="_self">caffeine</a></u> and <u><a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3933246/" target="_self">vitamin A</a></u> are proven to effectively targets stubborn cellulite on the calf area, helping to reduce the appearance of dimpling and improve skin texture and tone. Evertone’s <u><a href="https://evertoneskin.com/products/body-shaper" target="_self">cellulite cream</a></u> includes such ingredients in a non-greasy, fast-absorbing formula that leaves no residue, making it easy to apply and perfect for everyday use.</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-kTLmzF cNvxtt pf-161_"><b>Calf Exercises:</b> Regular exercise may help reduce cellulite, as long as it’s done progressively. Cardiovascular exercises such as running, cycling, and swimming can help to burn fat and improve circulation, while strength training exercises such as squats, lunges, and calf raises can help to build muscle to firm things up from below. </li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-kTLmzF cNvxtt pf-163_"><b>Exfoliation:</b> Any process that helps to increase circulation and remove dead skin cells will aid in your anti-cellulite efforts. Dead skin cell removal, in particular, may help speed the rate of skin cell regeneration, helping to thicken your skin. </li></ul></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-3b1c" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-fmciRz bheIgq pf-165_ pf-hide"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-gjNHFA gwWIgj"><div class="sc-ezbkAF A-dmbO pf-166_ pf-r pf-r-eh pf-hide" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:4"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gUQvok iVVDxu pf-167_"></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:8"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gUQvok iVVDxu pf-168_"><div data-pf-type="Block" class="sc-