dmbO pf-332_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gUQvok iVVDxu pf-333_"></div></div></div><p class="sc-jtXEFf jydWoQ pf-334_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jKTccl dCeBIC pf-336_">Having cellulite on the calves can be majorly frustrating.<br><br>Cellulite on the thighs or bum is common and easy to hide, but the calves are a different story. You may find that this type of cellulite impacts your self-esteem since you don’t see it on others as often. Plus, it can be visible even when you wear skirts or pants that cover your thighs.<br><br>Having cellulite on your calves is largely the result of how fat accumulates under your skin as well as the overall firmness and thickness of your skin. Other factors like hormones, age, and body weight can also play a role.<br><br>In this post, we’ll explain how you can reduce cellulite on the calves, so you can feel more confident about your leg!&nbsp;</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-cTAqQK eHolsa pf-337_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jKTccl dCeBIC pf-339_">Table Of Contents</span></h2><div class="sc-ezbkAF A-dmbO pf-340_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gUQvok iVVDxu pf-341_"><ul style="--text-indent:0;--line-spacing:10px" data-pf-type="List" class="sc-iFMAIt bKYNsx pf-342_"><li data-to-section="pf-baf4" data-offset="{&quot;all&quot;:50,&quot;laptop&quot;:50,&quot;tablet&quot;:50,&quot;mobile&quot;:50}" href="#" data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-iqVWFU eVpiLZ pf-343_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jKTccl dCeBIC pf-345_">1. <u>Proven Methods for Reducing Cellulite on Calves</u></span></li><li data-to-section="pf-8b0b" data-offset="{&quot;all&quot;:50,&quot;laptop&quot;:50,&quot;tablet&quot;:50,&quot;mobile&quot;:50}" href="#" data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-iqVWFU eVpiLZ pf-346_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jKTccl dCeBIC pf-348_">2. <u>Battling Calf Cellulite with Home Remedies</u></span></li><li data-to-section="pf-b440" data-offset="{&quot;all&quot;:50,&quot;laptop&quot;:50,&quot;tablet&quot;:50,&quot;mobile&quot;:50}" href="#" data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-iqVWFU eVpiLZ pf-349_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jKTccl dCeBIC pf-351_">3. <u>FAQ For How To Get Rid Of Cellulite On Your Calves</u></span></li></ul></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-9c33" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-fmciRz bheIgq pf-352_ pf-hide"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-gjNHFA gwWIgj"><div class="sc-ezbkAF A-dmbO pf-353_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:4"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gUQvok iVVDxu pf-354_"></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:8"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gUQvok iVVDxu pf-355_"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-cTAqQK eHolsa pf-356_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jKTccl dCeBIC pf-358_">Proven Methods for Reducing Cellulite on Calves</span></h2><div class="sc-ezbkAF A-dmbO pf-359_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gUQvok iVVDxu pf-360_"><p class="sc-jtXEFf jydWoQ pf-361_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jKTccl dCeBIC pf-363_">Cellulite can cause the skin to appear dimpled or lumpy, particularly on the legs and calves. If you are looking for ways to reduce the appearance of cellulite on your calves, there are several proven methods you can try.</span></p></div></div></div><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-cTAqQK eHolsa pf-364_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jKTccl dCeBIC pf-366_">Medical Treatments for Cellulite on Calves</span></h3><p class="sc-bBHHxi fhourC pf-367_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">If you're looking for a more aggressive solution to your calf cellulite, there are a few medical treatments that can help reduce the appearance of dimpling by breaking down fat and improving the tone and texture of your skin. Here are some of the most popular medical treatments for calf cellulite.</p><ul style="--text-indent:0;--line-spacing:10px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-eWfVMQ bsvuZZ pf-369_"><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-kTLmzF cNvxtt pf-370_"><b>Radiofrequency Therapy:</b> Radiofrequency therapy can help to reduce cellulite by improving skin elasticity and reducing the size of fat cells. </li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-kTLmzF cNvxtt pf-372_"><b>Laser Therapy:</b>&nbsp;Laser therapy uses focused light energy to penetrate the skin and target the underlying fat cells. This can help to break down fat and promote circulation. 
</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-kTLmzF cNvxtt pf-374_"><b>Ultrasound Therapy:</b>&nbsp;Ultrasound therapy with high-frequency sound waves targets the underlying fat cells while promoting the production of collagen, which helps to improve skin elasticity and thereby reduce the visiblity of cellulite.  </li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-kTLmzF cNvxtt pf-376_"><b><a href="https://dermnetnz.org/topics/mesotherapy" target="_self"></a>Mesotherapy:</b>&nbsp;<u><a href="https://dermnetnz.org/topics/mesotherapy" target="_self">Mesotherapy</a></u> is an injectable treatment that breaks down fat. A practitioner injects lipolytic agents to where the cellulite is located, which results in a reduction in cellulite. </li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-kTLmzF cNvxtt pf-378_"><b>Endermologie:</b>&nbsp;Endermologie massage therapy can help to improve circulation, reduce inflammation, and break down fat, leading to a reduction in cellulite.<b> </b></li></ul></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-e1e7" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-fmciRz bheIgq pf-380_ pf-hide"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-gjNHFA gwWIgj"><div class="sc-ezbkAF A-dmbO pf-381_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:4"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gUQvok iVVDxu pf-382_"></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:8"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gUQvok iVVDxu pf-383_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-cTAqQK eHolsa pf-384_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jKTccl dCeBIC pf-386_">Non-Medical Treatments for Cellulite on Calves</span></h3><p class="sc-bBHHxi fhourC pf-387_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">For most of us, these medical treatments can be too expensive and extreme. Thankfully, there are non-medical treatments you can incorporate into your self-care routine, to help break down that calf cellulite at home!&nbsp;</p><ul style="--text-indent:0;--line-spacing:10px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-eWfVMQ bsvuZZ pf-389_"><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-kTLmzF cNvxtt pf-390_"><b>Massage Your Calves:</b> Massage is one of the most effective methods of dealing with cellulite. A massage can help break down fluid <u><a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3359771/" target="_self">buildup and fascia</a></u> while improving circulation. This combination of effects can dramatically reduce cellulite on calves and other body parts, especially if you keep it up as a regular part of your body care regimen. For the massage to be effective, though, it’s important to apply enough pressure. This can be hard to do with the hands, but a <u><a href="https://evertoneskin.com/products/body-gua-sha-tool" target="_self">body gua sha tool </a></u>can make the process effortless.  </li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-kTLmzF cNvxtt pf-392_"><b>Topical Treatments:</b> Topical treatments for cellulite on the calves include creams, gels, and lotions. However, their effectiveness may vary depending on how they’re formulated. Look from products from brands like Evertone, that specialize in cellulite reduction cream for calves and other body parts. Ingredients like <u><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/17524126/" target="_self">caffeine</a></u> and <u><a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3933246/" target="_self">vitamin A</a></u> are proven to effectively targets stubborn cellulite on the calf area, helping to reduce the appearance of dimpling and improve skin texture and tone. Evertone’s <u><a href="https://evertoneskin.com/products/body-shaper" target="_self">cellulite cream</a></u> includes such ingredients in a non-greasy, fast-absorbing formula that leaves no residue, making it easy to apply and perfect for everyday use. 
</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-kTLmzF cNvxtt pf-394_"><b>Calf Exercises:</b> Regular exercise may help reduce cellulite, as long as it’s done progressively. Cardiovascular exercises such as running, cycling, and swimming can help to burn fat and improve circulation, while strength training exercises such as squats, lunges, and calf raises can help to build muscle to firm things up from below.   </li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-kTLmzF cNvxtt pf-396_"><b>Exfoliation:</b> Any process that helps to increase circulation and remove dead skin cells will aid in your anti-cellulite efforts. Dead skin cell removal, in particular, may help speed the rate of skin cell regeneration, helping to thicken your skin.  </li></ul></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-01da" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-fmciRz bheIgq pf-398_ pf-hide"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-gjNHFA gwWIgj"><div class="sc-ezbkAF A-dmbO pf-399_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:4"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gUQvok iVVDxu pf-400_"></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:8"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gUQvok iVVDxu pf-401_"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-cTAqQK eHolsa pf-402_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jKTccl dCeBIC pf-404_">Battling Calf Cellulite with Home Remedies</span></h2><p class="sc-bBHHxi fhourC pf-405_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">There are various <u><a href="https://evertoneskin.com/blogs/news/home-remedies-for-cellulite" target="_self">home remedies for cellulite</a></u> that can assist in minimizing the appearance of calf cellulite while helping to maintain a toned and smooth look of your calves. Unfortunately, the majority of suggestions on the internet don’t work, but these are a few things you may find beneficial.&nbsp;</p><ul style="--text-indent:0;--line-spacing:10px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-eWfVMQ bsvuZZ pf-407_"><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-kTLmzF cNvxtt pf-408_"><b>Exercise:</b>&nbsp;Aerobic exercise, such as running or cycling, is especially effective at targeting cellulite since it improves circulation while promoting fat loss. You can also try doing calf raises, squats, and lunges to build muscle in your calves.  </li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-kTLmzF cNvxtt pf-410_"><b>Hydrate:</b>&nbsp;Drink plenty of water each day to keep your skin hydrated. You can also try incorporating more water-rich fruits and vegetables into your diet, such as watermelon, cucumbers, and strawberries. 
</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-kTLmzF cNvxtt pf-412_"><b>Nourish Your Skin:</b> Moisturization can go a long way towards keeping your skin strong. When your skin is hydrated and fortified, it’ll look plumper and feel more elastic, which will allow it to appear smoother despite the dimpling below the skin. You can use any lotion on your calves, but for best results, it’s better to choose a product designed specifically for addressing cellulite.    </li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-kTLmzF cNvxtt pf-414_"><b>DIY Coffee Scrub:</b> Coffee scrub is an easy natural home remedy that can help with cellulite. Coffee grounds don’t include enough caffeine to impact your adipose tissue, but they do help remove dead skin and stimulate circualation. To make your own scrub, simply mix equal parts coffee grounds and coconut oil. Then massage into your calves for a few minutes in the shower.   </li></ul></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-e4c1" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-fmciRz bheIgq pf-416_ pf-hide"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-gjNHFA gwWIgj"><div class="sc-ezbkAF A-dmbO pf-417_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:4"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gUQvok iVVDxu pf-418_"></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:8"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gUQvok iVVDxu pf-419_"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-cTAqQK eHolsa pf-420_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jKTccl dCeBIC pf-422_">FAQ for How to Get Rid of Cellulite on Your Calves</span></h2><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dPiLbb JgHoc pf-423_">What are some natural remedies for cellulite on calves?</h3><p class="sc-bBHHxi fhourC pf-425_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><u><a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/149465" target="_blank"></a></u>Massage, exercise, topical caffeine products, and exfoliation are all excellent remedies for cellulite on calves. Other natural remedies, like apple cider vinegar or applying certain oils to the skin aren’t backed by scientifi, so there is no reason to believe they will work. </p><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dPiLbb JgHoc pf-427_">Can compression stockings help reduce the appearance of cellulite on the calves?</h3><p class="sc-bBHHxi fhourC pf-429_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">It’s easy to confuse cellulite on the calves with lipoedema, which is a chronic health condition that leads to fat buildup and can make the calves look swollen and dimpled. Compression stockings can help prevent lipoedema from worsening, but there is minimal evidence to suggest that they can reduce the appearance of cellulite on the calves.
